						<p>
							<strong>Good things to come?:</strong> &quot;In fact, the only time the Bears have won as convincingly as they did Sunday and failed to have a winning season was in 1996, when the Bears beat the defending Super Bowl champion Dallas Cowboys 22-6 on Monday Night Football at Soldier Field&quot; (Potash, 9/12, <a class="external" href="http://www.suntimes.com/sports/7615617-419/history-lesson-when-bears-open-well-they-close-well.html" target="_blank">Sun-Times</a>).<br />
