						</p>

						<p>
							<strong>Getting Paid:</strong> &quot;Robbie Gould put all seven of his kickoffs against the Falcons in the end zone, and five were touchbacks. Soon, he'll trigger an escalator clause in his contract. The clause pays him an extra $62,500 in 2012 for having eight touchbacks in a season. He had a career-high 16 last season and reached the mark in 2008 and 2009&quot; (Biggs, 9/13, <a class="external" href="http://www.chicagotribune.com/sports/football/bears/ct-spt-0913-bears-bits--20110913,0,6940983.story" target="_blank">Tribune</a>).
						</p>

						<p>
